text: The nomadic Suliban have been unified under the banner of the Romulan Empire. Now a stable and prosperous regime under their superpower allies, the Suliban seek even greater fortune in the scramble for Isogen, and Progenitor technologies. Their paranoid distrust of fellow Romulan allies like the Corvallen has driven the Suliban to ensure that the best interests of their collected alliance are served. Thus they have committed considerable force to a claim in the Origin Sector.

The Corvallen have taken an early interest in the Origin Sector on behalf of the Romulan Star Empire, under direct order of the Praetor. As the Romulans hold their line in the war against the Federation and the Klingons, they have entrusted expansion into this lucrative region to their most technologically advanced allies. The Corvallen see Progenitor technology and resources as the future of intergalactic civilization, and have placed themselves at the forefront of this exciting frontier.

After decades of silence, the Breen Confederacy have finally made their move. The most formidable warriors in the Alpha Quadrant have identified the value of Isogen and other Progenitor remnants, and decided to invest their front line in acquiring as much of it as possible. The Breen have struck a temporary alliance with the Corvallen to more efficiently research the Origin Sector, and with the Bolians to transform their ideas into reality. This mighty civilization is preparing for something big...

The Bolians have been a member of the Federation for a long time, but their hunger for exploration has been given a back seat in recent years, due to the ongoing war between the Federation, the Klingons, and the Romulans. The Origin Sector has given a subsection of the Bolian people a new sense of ambition, as they hope to bring Progenitor secrets and advancements back home. The Bolians were quick to move into this region and have made a bargain with the mighty Breen Confederacy in order to maintain their hold.

The Trill have inhabited this region of the Origin Sector in order to find an alternative home for their symbionts. Joined Trill have feared the implications of the Federation’s ongoing war with the Romulans and Klingons, and see opportunity in Progenitor resources and technology as a way of preserving their heritage. A tenuous coalition with the Tholian Assembly has assured some additional security as the rush for Isogen and its secrets overwhelms this region.

The Tholian Assembly have made their first major expansion into new territory with their claim to this region of the Origin Sector. This warrior race have been dormant for many years, biding their time to become a greater power in the Quadrant. The emergence of Progenitor ruins in this region gave them enough reason to advance, with their eye on getting any advantage they can against their age-old enemies, the Breen.

Raddan is home to some of the Vaara Expanse's wildest inhabitants. Roving bands of native hostiles seek to pillage any errant vessels that find themselves in this strange, inhospitable space. For this reason, and partly because of the regular solar flares from the system’s sun, the Raddan system has never been fully colonized.

Lydan was first discovered by a group of refugees in 2135. After a vicious attack on their homeworld, they fled to warp without a fully functioning navigation computer. Their ship ended up floating through this tumultuous space. Though it was an incredibly hard life, the refugees eventually managed to settle and tame a planet in Lydan, where a small colony lives to this day.

Tera Lara has some of the highest concentrations of dark matter ever recorded in a single star system. While dark matter makes up 85% of all space, it is rare to find a sample with greater density than a single proton mass for every three cubic meters. In Tera Lara, samples of Dark Matter have had a density rating almost triple that, which may contribute to the alarming frequency of subspace tears in the region.

The Bolians have been a member of the Federation for a long time, but their hunger for exploration has been given a back seat in recent years, due to the ongoing war between the Federation, the Klingons, and the Romulans. The Origin Sector has given a subsection of the Bolian people a new sense of ambition, as they hope to bring Progenitor secrets and advancements back home. The Bolians were quick to move into this region and have made a bargain with the mighty Breen Confederacy in order to maintain their hold.

The Trill have inhabited this region of the Origin Sector in order to find an alternative home for their symbionts. Joined Trill have feared the implications of the Federation’s ongoing war with the Romulans and Klingons, and see opportunity in Progenitor resources and technology as a way of preserving their heritage. A tenuous coalition with the Tholian Assembly has assured some additional security as the rush for Isogen and its secrets overwhelms this region.
